FCE Bank Plc, a unit of  Ford Motor
Co. (F) , is selling 250 million pounds of bonds due in 2017,
according to two people with knowledge of the sale.  The notes may be priced to yield about 5 percent, the
people said. BNP Paribas SA, Deutsche Bank AG,  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) 
and Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc are managing the deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
